        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-31T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="261" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On November 10 the Foreign Ministers of the United States, United Kingdom, and
                    France, meeting in Paris to discuss the German question, agreed to discourage
                    other nations from taking steps that would lead to <hi rend="italic">de
                        facto</hi> or <hi rend="italic">de jure</hi> recognition of the “German
                    Democratic Republic”. For a record of their discussion of policy toward the
                    “German Democratic Republic”, see telegram 4716, <ref target="#pg_305">p.
                        305</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
